One man has been killed and seven others injured when a minibus and light motor vehicle collided on the N2 in Somerset West, Western Cape on Sunday.On arrival, paramedics found two wrecked vehicles on the side of the road. Both vehicles had sustained a heavy amount of damage in the collision.The body of a man was found trapped inside the minibus. It was unfortunate that there was nothing that could be done for the man as he had sustained several injuries. He was declared dead at the scene.Several other patients were found on the scene. One was in a critical condition while two others were found in a serious condition. Four other patients were found with moderate injuries.Advanced life support interventions were provided to the critically and seriously injured patients and once treated, they were transported to Tygerberg and Helderberg Hospitals for further care.The details surrounding this incident are not yet known.-TNA Reporter 